Question: Ginger and Amy both start with 100 pieces of Halloween candy. Ginger eats 4 pieces a day and Amy eats 3 pieces a day. How much more candy does Amy have after two weeks?
--------------------------------------------------
Generation:

First, we need to determine how many pieces of candy each of Amy and Ginger will eat in two weeks. 
Ginger eats 4 pieces a day, so in two weeks4 \times 7 \times 2 = 56 pieces.
Amy eats 3 pieces a day, so in two weeks3 \times 7 \times 2 = 42 pieces.
Next, we calculate the amount of candy each person has left after two weeks.
Ginger starts with 100 pieces and eats 56 pieces, so she has100 - 56 = 44 pieces left.
Amy starts with 100 pieces and eats 42 pieces, so she has100 - 42 = 58 pieces left.
Finally, we find the difference in the amount of candy between Amy and Ginger.
The difference is 58 - 44 = 14 pieces.
</reasoning>
