Question: Ginger and Amy both start with 100 pieces of Halloween candy. Ginger eats 4 pieces a day and Amy eats 3 pieces a day. How much more candy does Amy have after two weeks?
--------------------------------------------------
Generation:

First, we need to determine how many pieces of candy each person eats in two weeks. Ginger eats 4 pieces a day, so in 14 days, she eats \(4 \times 14 = 56\) pieces. Amy eats 3 pieces a day, so in 14 days, she eats \(3 \times 14 = 42\) pieces. Next, we calculate the amount of candy each person has left after two weeks. Ginger starts with 100 pieces and eats 56, so she has \(100 - 56 = 44\) pieces left. Amy starts with 100 pieces and eats 42, so she has \(100 - 42 = 58\) pieces left. Finally, we find the difference in the amount of candy Amy Amy has compared to Ginger, which is \(58 - 44 = 14\) pieces.
</ing>
<answer>
\boxed{14}
</answer><|eot_id|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|><|endoftext|>
